Procedure (Simple Words):

1. Go to the Spring Initializr website.


2. Choose Maven, Java, and Spring Boot version 3 or above.


3. Add Spring Web as a dependency.


4. Download the project and open it in your IDE.


5. Create two packages: model and controller.


6. In the model package, create a Student.java class.


7. In the controller package, create StudentController.java with all CRUD methods.


8. Run the project using the command mvn spring-boot:run.


9. Open Postman and test the API links for GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE.
